Drift ships 12 built-in themes: default (vibrant bright ANSI), minimal (status colors only), monochrome (bold/dim only, no color), high-contrast (max brightness, no dimming), dark (tuned for dark backgrounds), light (tuned for light backgrounds, basic colors, no dim), protanopia (red-green color blind friendly: blue/yellow/cyan only), solarized-dark, solarized-light, gruvbox, nord, dracula (designer palettes using 256-color codes, all MIT-licensed). Users select via --theme=NAME. The default theme when color is active is "default". Unknown theme names fall back to default with no error. See <ref spec="output.theme_system">theme system</ref> and <ref spec="output_impl.theme_definitions">theme definitions</ref>.